jobDescription:
What makes this role unique: The type of work we have ranges from doing greenfield development, to support and lifecycle. This work includes API development, UI development and back-end application development for overnight processing. Projects vary, but currently we are working on tax document processing, automation of trade processing, and development of services to support applications being built for branch offices.  

 Candidate Profile: 

.NET Generalist with strong preference for experience writing/using web services. See above for more detail 
Preferred: C#, T-SQL, Web API, JavaScript 
A plus to have: SSIS, MVC, CA Autosys, Azure development, Angular 
Strong SQL skills 
Experience with Test Driven Development 
Exposure to Entity Framework or other ORM 
 

Qualities Needed: 

Good communicator who wants to work in a team environment, comfortable performing pair programming 
Analytical – not afraid to dive into complex code and data to troubleshoot issues 
Creative problem solver who is automation focused – we’re looking to not have recurring work come back to us, but to better automate or teach/train users for self service 
Motivated by small quick wins and process improvement 
Comfortable working in an agile environment.? Prefer experience working in agile 
 

Benefits to being placed at company: 

Long-term contract with potential for extended renewals 
Team focused environment.? We treat our consultants as part of the team. 
Rich developer community with lunch & learns on best practices. ?Focus on software craftsmanship. 
A DevOps culture. We use automated deployment and are constantly looking to improve in the DevOps space. Our DBAs/App Admins are part of our collaboration. 
Agile/lean practices with diversity of projects
